Southwestern Bell Corp said itopposes the Department of Justice recommendation that regionalholding companies be banned from offering interexchangeservices within their regions.    Southwestern Bell said state regulators should decidewhether regional holding companies are allowed to provide theservice, according to a brief filed in U.S. district court inWashington outlining the company's position.    The company contends there is little likelihood competitionwould be hampered, according to the brief.     Southwestern Bell supports the Justice Department'srecommendation to lift bans on information services andequipment manufacturing, and to allow regional holdingcompanies to enter non-telecommunications businesses, it said. Reuter&#3;